"""
Explanation of the code:

This numpy script is meant to process the readings form the Picoscope.
it takes n ammount of samples. With 8000 values each. Adscribe the samples to a list.
From the length of the list a 3D np array is created. Its dimensions correspond to the 
N#_Samples x N#_Parameters x N#_Values. The parameters are: Time, ADC, Voltage, Bdot, B, I 
The N# of parameters is fixed to 6 as is the N# of values to 8000. 

The conversions to units are not so important. But how to have a 3D array which can be compatible with the other different arays is
To do that during operation the NP arrays should be  stored into a list . The length of the list will dictate the Sample dimension of the 3D array
Then with the list itslef you can index the value of each 1D array inside of it and introduce it into the 3d array
Then the 3d array can modify itslef calculating the specific values for each parameter of each value







"""






